In male patients (
Table 4
) ANOVA revealed a significant effect (F = 10.09; p = 0.002) of the 5HT2A genotype on the delusions score. After Bonferroni correction, differences still remained in delusion scores: homozygotes for the minor allele A had significantly lower scores than men who were homozygotes or heterozygotes for the T allele (2.86 ± 1.21 and 1.71 ± 1.44).
